The last-minute fight to save Gaza's ancient archaeological treasures
subhed: Amid the vast destruction of the war, a small group of determined individuals fought to save Gaza's archaeological heritage. On September 10, they secured a few hours' reprieve from the Israeli army before a storage depot filled with artifacts was bombed to perform a delicate evacuation – the result of intense, high-level negotiations.

subhed: More than 1,000 people from across the city flocked to the housing complex in Hong Kong's northern Tai Po district to pay their respects on Sunday. Authorities have set up a task force to look into the cause of the blaze.

title: Honduran voters to judge record of country's first left-wing president, Xiomara Castro
subhed: Presidential, legislative and municipal elections take place on Sunday in the Central American nation. Outgoing President Xiomara Castro has devoted most of her term to tackling insecurity. Donald Trump has called on voters to support the right-wing candidate.

title: Kikuo Ibe's quest to build the unbreakable watch
subhed: Forty-two years after inventing the first indestructible watch, the Casio G-Shock, the Japanese engineer continues to inspire. As part of a European tour, he stopped in France to meet his fans.

title: 'Dédé la Sardine' and Russian oil: Inside the affair that has haunted Total for 15 years
subhed: Seven people have been ordered to stand trial for their involvement in an arbitration process that was allegedly manipulated in order to extract the equivalent of €16 billion from French oil company Total. Their trial begins on Monday.

subhed: The all-powerful head of the presidential administration was deeply unpopular in Ukraine. Yet his departure comes at the worst time, as Kyiv faces mounting pressure from the US to strike a peace deal with Russia.

title: China's invisible workforce powering the platform economy
subhed: Service, delivery and mobility apps are shaping China's new economy. In a society with minimal safety nets, they promise frontline workers higher incomes, at the price of long hours and extreme physical effort.

title: Inside the archives of shoemaker Roger Vivier
subhed: This star shoemaker of the 1930s through the 1990s spent his long career experimenting with all kinds of designs. His archives, a testament to his boundless creativity, are now housed in a Parisian hôtel particulier.
